    <h2>The Market for Short .com Domains</h2>

    <p>Three-character .com domains are finite assets. The namespace is fixed — no new 3-character combinations can be created. As digital presence becomes increasingly important for businesses worldwide, the supply of premium short domains remains constant while demand grows.</p>

    <p>Factors that influence the value of short .com domains:</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Length</strong> — shorter domains command higher prices. Three characters is near the minimum for a meaningful .com</li>
      <li><strong>Meaning</strong> — domains that form recognizable words, abbreviations, or industry terms are valued over random strings</li>
      <li><strong>Extension</strong> — .com remains the most trusted and valuable TLD by a significant margin</li>
      <li><strong>Age</strong> — continuous registration history adds trust and authority</li>
      <li><strong>Clean history</strong> — domains without spam, malware, or penalty history carry their full potential</li>
    </ul>

    <aside class="article-cta">
